paragraphs:
[16]
The Investigator's report (the "Report") dated May 31, 2013, identified six grounds for the complaint as follows:
1. Mr. Stinson O'Gorman demeaned the Applicant;
2. Mr. Stinson obstructed the Applicant's opportunity to work in Aboriginal Affairs;
3. Mr. Stinson O'Gorman set the Applicant up for failure;
4. Mr. Stinson O'Gorman insulted the Applicant in an email;
5. Mr. Stinson O'Gorman threatened the Applicant in relation to his ATIP request; and
6. Mr. Stinson O'Gorman made false accusations about the Applicant so that he could hire a friend.
